
@context "Data Directory Analysis"
@target_directory "d:\GodoTDev\mutanic-reign-Working-main\data"

@overview "Data Architecture"
  - "Philosophy": Heavy use of Godot `Resource` files (`.tres`) for data-driven design.
  - "State Management": Separation of 'Definition' (Type) and 'Instance' (State).
    - Example: `CaravanType` (Static Config) vs `CaravanState` (Runtime Data).
  
@key_scripts
  - "BuildSlotState.gd": Lightweight container for building persistence (Scene + Level).
  - "HubState.gd": Massive state container for Settlements (Inventory, Slots, Population).
  - "CaravanState.gd": Runtime logic for traders, wrapping `CharacterSheet`.

@structure
  - "BeastDens": Spawner configurations.
  - "Caravans": Trader definitions.
  - "Hubs": Settlement initial states.
  - "Items": Economic commodities.
  - "Skills": RPG progression trees.
  - "troops": Military unit definitions.
